The paper deals with the efficient storage and partitioning of sparse matrices, which is a common problem in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which deals with the efficient organization and manipulation of data. The paper also involves numerical methods and optimization, which suggests the categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses statistical evaluation and comparison of different methods, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
